Taking the overall nett title with an impressive score of 130 nett was Fr Richard Kabuthi, who beat Evans Ngene by 10 shots, while Simon Karari on 142 finished a shot better than Mike Ngene.  At Vet Lab, lady golfer Patricia Gichuru carded 41 points o beat men winner Isaac Makokha by one point for the overall title during the Mary Maingi’s Year Opener golf tournament.
Gichuru posted 16 points in the first nine and 25 points at the back nine, while the Kenya Amateur Match Play champion Makokha, currently preparing for the Magical Kenya Open, posted 20 points in each nine for an excellent 40 points, which earned him the men’s top prize after beating X.N.Iraki and David Evans on countback.



